### Start Redis (leave window open)
### ```powershell
### & "$env:TEMP\Redis\redis-server.exe"
### ```

### Start Celery Worker (in a new activated venv window)
### ```powershell
### $env:PYTHONPATH = "C:\Users\Ndegwa\Desktop\qb-data-loader"
### celery -A app.tasks.import_tasks:celery_app worker --loglevel=info

### Start Uvicorn Server (in another new activated venv window)

#uvicorn app.main:app --reload

# Useful Docker Commands for the Future
# 
# Stop Redis: docker stop qb-redis
# Start it again: docker start qb-redis
# Remove (if you ever want to clean up): docker rm qb-redis (after stopping)
# View logs: docker logs qb-redis
